# Timed Drill: Profit & Loss (Day 05)

Time Limit: 5 minutes. Answer ALL questions quickly.

1. CP = ₹200, SP = ₹250. Profit% = ?
   A) 20%   B) 25%   C) 30%   D) 35%

2. If an item is sold at 10% loss for ₹540, find CP.
   A) ₹594   B) ₹600   C) ₹610   D) ₹630

3. Discount of 15% on ₹800 = ?
   A) ₹100   B) ₹110   C) ₹120   D) ₹130

4. Buying at ₹80 and selling at ₹100. Profit% = ?
   A) 20%   B) 25%   C) 30%   D) 35%

5. Two successive discounts: 10% + 20% on ₹1000. Final SP = ?
   A) ₹680   B) ₹700   C) ₹720   D) ₹750

6. A 25% profit means SP = ? × CP
   A) 1.15   B) 1.20   C) 1.25   D) 1.30

7. Loss of 12.5% on ₹640 = ?
   A) ₹72   B) ₹80   C) ₹88   D) ₹96

8. MP = ₹500, SP = ₹400. Discount% = ?
   A) 10%   B) 15%   C) 20%   D) 25%

9. Successive discounts of 50% and 50% on ₹1000 = ?
   A) ₹250   B) ₹500   C) ₹100   D) ₹50

10. Selling 5 items for the price of 8. Profit% = ?
    A) 50%   B) 60%   C) 66.67%   D) 75%
